<p><strong>Dogecoin</strong> (<strong>DOGE,</strong> <strong>&ETH;</strong>) is a <a title="Cryptocurrency" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cryptocurrency">cryptocurrency</a> created by software engineers Billy Markus and Jackson Palmer, who decided to create a payment system that is free from traditional banking fees. Dogecoin features the face of the <a title="Shiba Inu" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shiba_Inu">Shiba Inu</a> dog from the "<a title="Doge (meme)" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Doge_(meme)">Doge</a>" <a title="Internet meme" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Internet_meme">meme</a> as its logo and namesake. It was introduced on December 6, 2013, and quickly developed its own <a title="Online community" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Online_community">online community</a>, reaching a market capitalization of US $85,314,347,523 on May 5, 2021.</p>
